The article, written by Amy Chua for The Wall Street Journal, highlights Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh's role as a mentor for young lawyers, particularly women. It mentions that a quarter of Kavanaugh's clerks have been members of minority groups, and more than half have been women. Chua personally helped place 10 Yale Law School students with Kavanaugh, eight of them being women. The article quotes these clerks praising Kavanaugh's work ethic, commitment to excellence, humility, and decency. They also describe him as an extraordinary mentor who feels a sense of responsibility for each of his clerks.